# ❌ DO NOT USE THIS FILE ❌
#
# .env.local files are PROHIBITED in this codebase.
# Credentials in files can be accidentally committed to git.
#
# DELETE any .env.local file you created.
#
# ✅ INSTEAD: Use AWS Secrets Manager (same as production)
#
# Setup takes 5 minutes:
#   See LOCAL_CRED_SETUP.md for complete instructions
#
# Quick start:
#   aws secretsmanager create-secret --name db/password --secret-string "your_password"
#   aws secretsmanager create-secret --name db/host --secret-string "localhost"
#   ...then run: python3 run-all-loaders.py
#
# That's it. No files. Credentials stored securely in AWS.
